Important: Each break‑glass user exists only in its own account and can only access that account. 

How Break‑Glass Access Works 

1. bg-admin controls access 

In each account, the bg-admin user can: 

Enable console login (create login profile) 

Disable console login (delete login profile) 

Reset passwords 

Manage MFA devices 

View break‑glass user details 

 

2. Team member logs in 

Once bg-admin enables console login: 

User logs in with username + temporary password 

User is placed in restricted mode until MFA is configured 

 

3. User sets up MFA 

Each break‑glass user must configure MFA in their own account before ReadOnlyAccess becomes active. 

 

4. User performs emergency read‑only investigation 

After MFA is enabled, the user receives full ReadOnlyAccess. 

 

5. bg-admin disables console login after the outage 

This prevents unauthorized use. 

 

 

 

How to Login During an Outage 

 

Step 1 — Request Access 

Contact your manager or the break‑glass admin. They will: 

Enable your console login 

Generate a temporary password 

Provide the login URL for your specific AWS account 

Example login URL: https://<AccountID>.signin.aws.amazon.com/console 

 

 

Step 2 — Login 

Go to the account’s login URL 

Enter your username 

Enter the temporary password 

You will be prompted to set a new password 

You will enter restricted mode until MFA is configured 

 

Step 3 — Set Up MFA (Required Before Use) 

Click your username → Security Credentials 

Select Assign MFA device 

Choose Virtual MFA device 

Scan the QR code using: 

Microsoft Authenticator 

Google Authenticator 

Enter two consecutive MFA codes 

Log out and log back in with MFA 

Once MFA is active, your ReadOnlyAccess permissions will work. 

What You Can Do During an Outage 

After MFA is enabled: 

Investigate issues 

View logs 

View resources 

Gather information for incident response 

Update the incident ticket 

 

 

You cannot: 

Create resources 

Modify resources 

Delete resources 

Change configurations 

Break‑glass access is strictly read‑only. 

 

Password Management 

Passwords are: 

Generated by bg-admin 

Stored in a secure password vault 

Rotated after each outage 

Disabled when the outage ends 

Users cannot reset their own break‑glass passwords. 

 

Alerts You Will Trigger 

1. Break‑Glass Console Login Detected 

Sent when any break‑glass user logs in. 

Includes: 

Username 

Source IP 

Timestamp 

MFA used or not 

 

 

 

2. Break‑Glass IAM Activity Detected 

Sent when any break‑glass user performs an IAM API call. 

Includes: 

Username 

IAM action 

Source IP 

Timestamp 

These alerts go to the security team for verification. 

Quarterly Maintenance Tasks 

1. Access Review 

Confirm each break‑glass user still requires access 

Validate employment status 

Ensure MFA devices are active 

Review login history 

. Policy Review 

Validate MFA enforcement 

Validate alerting rules 

Validate admin permissions 

 
